@zjffdu 
I have had very good experience with this feature in my environment and would like to include it in the master so that further development can be based on it.
Since I have been using this feature, Zeppelin does not run in any OOM when I look at all the notes via script.

@zjffdu 
I want to try to solve the concurrent problem in pull request #4252 with a ReentrantReadWriteLock. This solution should also catch this pull request.

Give me some time for the implementation.

@zjffdu 
I have changed the implementation to Read/Write-Lock and the CI is also successful. A new review would be nice.
Sorry for this big change, but protecting the Note object with a read/write lock requires big changes in several classes.

> Not directly, I think it's a different problem. When a paragraph is executed, the result is not displayed until the paragraph is clicked..
@Reamer Oh, what's your code version,  I can't reproduce that phenomenon on my 0.10.0 code version, sounds like the result is hidden
And the PR is run failed, whether you can force merge it

